node.text:
If quarantine taught me anything, it’s that we all crave some form of connectivity, even people who consider themselves introverts (like myself). 

Let’s all get vaccinated so we can get back to traveling the world. 🌎

It’s easier than ever to get vaccinated. Visit vaccines.gov to find the closest vaccine location to you. Together, #WeCanDoThis and end the pandemic! 😷

node.text:
Can someone please explain the weather in Boston? It’s raining and muggy, and I have the AC on full blast during a full rainstorm. Also, there’s pink lightning. 

How is everyone else holding up on their Wednesday? Mine is like the weather today. 😂🤤

#boston #visitboston #igboston

It was 96 degrees in Boston so I decided it was a good idea to cut my own hair…hence, the space buns. Some quarantine habits just seem to stick. 😂

Also, figure skating should actually be a summer sport because I’m sprinting to the rink to cool down. 🤤❄️

node.text:
As athletes, our dreams start a long time ago. It takes years of camps, competitions, and training. During our annual skating camp in 2013, a gymnastics camp was going on at the same time. We ended up interacting with some of the junior kids, and it’s been an adventure watching their journeys through social media. Some have retired and some have even qualified for the Olympics. Even though it’s a completely different sport, it’s intensely exciting to see these athletes go for their dreams with 1000% focus. Here’s a photo of me trying to stay calm before the storm. 

Who’s watching #gymtrials21 and cheering insanely loudly at the tv? 📣

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Mirai Nagasu on June 26, 2021 tagging @onherturf. May be an image of 1 person, standing and indoor.

Photo by Mirai Nagasu on June 26, 2021. May be an image of 3 people and text that says 'UNITED STATES OLYMPIC TEAM U.S. OLYMPIC TEAM TRIALS GYMNASTICS JUNE 24 -27 NBCSN peacock 999 OLYMPIC HOME.DF USA CHANNEL SAM MIKULAK SUNI LEE SIMONE BILES'.
Photo shared by Mirai Nagasu on June 25, 2021 tagging @webtoonofficial, @advancingjustice_aajc, and @88rising. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text:
When I called my parents to catch up with them, they told me to be careful when walking in public and to avoid eye contact with strangers. The fact that my parents are worried about their own safety is not okay. I think it’s more important than ever to voice my pride in my background and story. Thank you to @webtoonofficial for taking the time to illustrate a small piece of mine. I hope that another restaurant baby like me has big dreams and is going after them like I was able to. ♥️

#stopasianhate #webtoon
